Hanson Industries, the U.S. arm ofHanson Trust PLC, said contracts have been exchanged in Londonfor the sale of Bond's Delivery Service to Rockwood HoldingsPLC for about 6.0 mln dlrs in cash.    Completion is subject to Rockwood shareholder approval.    In its most recent financial year, Bond's which waspurchasedby Hanson Trust Plc in its acquisition of Imperial Group PLC inApril 1986, made 960,000 dlrs pre-tax profit on sales of 13.6mln dlrs.    Net tangible assets are 5.2 mln dlrs, Hanson said. Reuter&#3;